foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: FAA - The number of requests pending as of start of the fiscal year is 66 lower than reported in last year's annual report as pending at the end of FY 2010. The adjustment primarily reflects reqeusts where final action was taken by all appropriate FAA offices in FY 2010, but not all database closures were entered into the database until FY 2011. (Note: FOIA requests assigned to multiple FAA offices are not closed until the last FAA office responds to the requester.)

FMCSA - The number of requests pending as of the start of the fiscal year is 3 higher than reported in last year's annual report as pending at the end of FY 2010. This is because 3 additional FOIA requests were received in FY 2010, but they were not logged into the system before the end of FY 2010.

RITA - The number of requests pending as of the start of the fiscal year is 1 higher than reported in last year's annual report as pending at the end of FY 2010. This is because 1 additional FOIA request was received in FY 2010, but it was not logged into the system before the end of FY 2010.
Agency Overall - For the reasons stated above, the number pending at the start of the fiscal year is 62 lower than reported in last year's annual report as pending at the end of FY 2010.

foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: The number of FAA appeals pending at the beginning of the fiscal year is one less than reported at the end of FY 2010. This is the result of an appeal that was closed in FY 2010, but not closed out in the system by the end of FY 2010.

The number of MARAD appeals pending at the beginning of the fiscal year is one more than reported at the end of FY 2010. This is the result of an appeal that was received in FY 2010, but not logged into the system by the end of FY 2010.
